This paper deals with autonomous vehicles and their control methods, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also mentions the use of differential game theory and machine learning techniques, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). The experimental results presented in the paper involve racing and competition, which could be categorized under game theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.LG) as well.
